The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Royalty on coal set 

for recast

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Dec. 5: The recommendations of the committee constituted by the coal ministry on the issue of revision of royalty rates on coal and lignite will soon be placed before the cabinet committee on economic affairs for a decision.

 Meanwhile, the mines ministry has constituted a study group under the chairmanship of the additional secretary to consider the next revision of royalty rates on major minerals other than coal, lignite and sand for stowing, minister of state for coal Dasari Narayan Rao told Lok Sabha today. He also said that the Economic Advisory Council (EAC) to the Prime Minister had made certain recommendations on the issue of payment of royalty for coal on ad valorem basis versus tonnage basis.

 According to EAC, the royalty may be shifted from specific levy to a combination of specific and ad valorem levies.




